.TH DFS-SEARCH 1 "2025" "DFS Search Tools 3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dfs-search \- depth-first search file finder with modern C++20/23
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dfs-search
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I pattern
[\fIdirectory\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dfs-search
performs depth-first search through directory hierarchies to find files
matching specified patterns. It supports wildcard patterns, regex matching,
parallel execution, multiple output formats, and advanced features like
duplicate detection and content searching.

Built with modern C++20/23 features for high performance and ease of use.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-depth " " \fIN\fR
Set maximum search depth (default: 10)
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-regex
Use regular expression pattern matching instead of wildcards
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output showing search progress and errors
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-parallel
Enable parallel search using multiple threads
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-threads " " \fIN\fR
Number of threads to use for parallel search (default: hardware_concurrency)
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " \fIFMT\fR
Output format: plain, colored, json, xml, csv (default: colored)
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-duplicates
Find and report duplicate files based on content hash
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-content " " \fIPATTERN\fR
Search file contents for specified pattern (uses memory-mapped I/O)
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-config " " \fIFILE\fR
Load configuration from specified file
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-exclude " " \fIPATH\fR
Exclude directory path from search (can be specified multiple times)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit

.SH PATTERN MATCHING
.SS Wildcard Patterns
.TP
.B *.txt
Match all files ending with .txt
.TP
.B test*
Match all files starting with 'test'
.TP
.B *config*
Match all files containing 'config'
.TP
.B *
Match all files

.SS Regular Expressions
Use the
.B \-r
flag to enable regex pattern matching:
.TP
.B .*\\.cpp
Match all .cpp files
.TP
.B test_.*\\.txt
Match files like test_foo.txt, test_bar.txt
.TP
.B [0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}\\.log
Match date-formatted log files

.SH OUTPUT FORMATS
.TP
.B plain
Simple text output without colors
.TP
.B colored
Colored terminal output with emoji and formatting (default)
.TP
.B json
JSON format suitable for scripting and processing
.TP
.B xml
XML format for integration with other tools
.TP
.B csv
CSV format for spreadsheet import

.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
.B dfs-search
looks for configuration files in the following order:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
./.dfsrc
.IP \(bu 2
~/.dfsrc
.IP \(bu 2
/etc/dfsrc
.RE

Configuration file format (key=value):
.RS
.nf
# Maximum search depth
max_depth=15

# Enable parallel search
parallel=true
threads=8

# Output format
format=json

# Excluded paths
exclude=/proc
exclude=/sys
exclude=/tmp
.fi
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B dfs-search '*.txt' /home/user
Find all .txt files in /home/user with default depth
.TP
.B dfs-search -r '.*\\.cpp' -d 15 ./src
Find all .cpp files using regex, searching up to depth 15
.TP
.B dfs-search -p -t 8 '*.log' /var/log
Parallel search for .log files using 8 threads
.TP
.B dfs-search --format json '*.conf' /etc > results.json
Output results in JSON format to a file
.TP
.B dfs-search -D '*.jpg' ~/Pictures
Find and report duplicate JPEG files
.TP
.B dfs-search -c 'TODO' '*.cpp' ./src
Find .cpp files containing the text 'TODO'
.TP
.B dfs-search -e /tmp -e /var '*.txt' /
Search entire filesystem excluding /tmp and /var

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.dfsrc
User configuration file
.TP
.I /etc/dfsrc
System-wide configuration file

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate ~/.dfsrc configuration file

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Files found successfully
.TP
.B 1
No files found or error occurred

.SH PERFORMANCE
.B dfs-search
is optimized for performance with:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Compiled with -O3 -march=native optimization flags
.IP \(bu 2
Memory-mapped I/O for content searching
.IP \(bu 2
Multi-threaded parallel search capability
.IP \(bu 2
Efficient path exclusion filtering
.RE

Typical performance: 10,000-15,000 files/second on modern hardware

